---
title: Time to Slack
---

<section class="page-header">
  <%= image_tag "hourglass.png", class: "logo" %>
  <h1 class="title">Time to Slack</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Automatic time zone conversions for your team</p>
  <%= partial "add_to_slack" %>
</section>

<section class="page-content">
  <div class="content-row -reverse">
    <div class="item description-paragraph">
      <h1 class="title">Detects time zones</h1>
      <p class="body">
        Don't ask if that the time is in your time zone or your
        teammate's time zone. Slack Time automatically parses the phrase
        and converts the times for everybody in the room.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="item">
      <%= image_tag "screenshot.png", class: "image-responsive" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="content-row">
    <div class="item description-paragraph">
      <h1 class="title">Permissions</h1>
      <p class="body">
        Here are the permissions that <strong>Time to Slack</strong> needs and why:
        <ul>
          <li>Confirm user's identity: Default permission for Slack apps</li>
          <li>Add commands: to add the <code>/time</code> command</li>
          <li>Access the team's profile information: to find each team member's time zone</li>
          <li>Access information about user's public channels: to be able to match channel members with their time zone</li>
          <li>Send messages as user: to post the modified message with time zone information</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
